			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Us</strong><br />
At MediaCore we are helping change the world of education through video. Universities, schools and organizations all over the world are realizing that video is an incredibly compelling tool for enabling anyone to learn anywhere, anytime. MediaCore provides an award-winning platform that takes the complexity out of capturing video, building a media library, storing content, and delivering an exceptional learning experience to users viewing content on both desktop and mobile browsers. We&#39;re currently working with large universities and innovative schools all over the world helping them educate and train millions of people. If you&rsquo;re passionate about education and want to work with an incredible team on building tools that are helping make a substantial impact in global education standards then MediaCore is for you.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Role</strong><br />
MediaCore is looking for a highly motivated and experienced front-end web developer with a proven track record. You will be working within a small multi-disciplinary team of educators, designers and developers - so everyone is a thinker, a problem-solver, and plays a critical role in delivering the products that make our customers and their users happy. We are a nimble, high-energy startup, so this is a great opportunity for you to make your mark.</p>
<p>
<strong>What you&rsquo;ll be doing</strong><br />
The position will involve a prominent role in furthering development of MediaCore&rsquo;s flagship product. You will be responsible for building high-quality, pixel-perfect, front-end application components that tightly integrate with our back-end systems. You will work closely with the design team to turn ideas, requirements and mockups into production-ready code using UI/UX best practices. The position is full-time.</p>
<p>
<strong>Your must haves</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Expert knowledge of JavaScript</li>
<li>
Expert knowledge of fundamental web technologies (e.g. HTML/CSS)</li>
<li>
Ability to write high-performance, reusable code for UI components</li>
<li>
Aware of but not reliant on Object Oriented JavaScript Frameworks (MooTools, Google Closure)</li>
<li>
Experience developing rich applications with HTML/CSS/JS</li>
<li>
3+ years of experience building web applications</li>
<li>
Ability to work independently as well as part of a team</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Preference will be given to applicants who have experience in any of the following</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Well-developed knowledge of database technologies including MySQL</li>
<li>
Experience with Google Closure and Mootools</li>
<li>
Experience with Python and PHP</li>
<li>
Experience with RESTful APIs</li>
<li>
Experience using Vim and Git as development tools</li>
<li>
Ability to navigate deep into Photoshop layers to export slices and make sprites</li>
</ul>
<p>
<em>Great Ideas.</em><br />
We&rsquo;re really passionate about solving big problems facing educational institutions as they look to increase student outcomes.</p>
<p>
Video is increasingly becoming a huge component of the way that many people learn globally and we&rsquo;re only starting to see how video can help all kinds of educational institutions and are always looking for new ideas on where to take our products next. We&rsquo;d love to hear some of your ideas on how video and technology could be integrated into educational institutions.</p>
<p>
<em>Award Winning Technology.</em><br />
If you enjoy working with engineers and designers who build really awesome software, then look no further. FastCompany just ranked MediaCore as one of the &ldquo;Top 10 Most Innovative Companies in Digital Video&rdquo; and while we&rsquo;ve been thrilled with that nomination (along with 8 other awards we&rsquo;ve won this year), we&rsquo;re really motivated by coming into work every day and just building a great product that&rsquo;s solving real problems.</p>
<p>
Our team is passionate about Open Source technology. We love Git, Python, Ruby, Google Closure, FFMPEG, and HTML5, but we especially love combining all these things with design and aesthetics that are unrivaled in our industry and are making a big impact in the classroom.</p>
<p>
<em>Startup Mentality.</em><br />
We&rsquo;re not a big company and sometimes we all need to chip in to get the job done. This is the way things happen at a startup. You must be prepared to go beyond your role and appreciate that our nimbleness is actually our greatest strength.</p>
<p>
<em>Energy.</em><br />
We&rsquo;re a pretty flexible employer, but when we do work it needs to be energetic and inspirational to those around us. You need to be hands-on, passionate, persistent, creative and easy to deal with. Ultimately you want to get things done with a high personal productivity.</p>
<p>
<em>Adaptability.</em><br />
Being able to adapt to change when necessary is important for us. As a fast-growing company, we are often changing gears and shifting focus onto new features, goals and priorities. We value those who are able to keep up with those shifts.</p>
<p>
<em>Fun.</em><br />
We want you to enjoy coming to work each day. We&rsquo;ve been known to host some pretty awesome social events - from pirate parties on tall ships to camping trips to wine tastings at local vineyards. If you like to have fun once in awhile, you&rsquo;ll definitely want to consider working for us.</p>
]]></description>
