<strong>About MediaCore</strong><br />
At MediaCore we are helping change the world of education through video. Universities, schools and organizations all over the world are realizing that video is an incredibly compelling tool for enabling anyone to learn anywhere, anytime. MediaCore provides an award-winning platform that takes the complexity out of capturing video, building a media library, storing content, and delivering an exceptional learning experience to users viewing content on both desktop and mobile browsers. We&#39;re currently working with large universities and innovative schools all over the world helping them educate and train millions of people. If you&rsquo;re passionate about education and want to work with an incredible team on building tools that are helping make a substantial impact in global education standards then MediaCore is for you.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Role</strong><br />
MediaCore is growing rapidly in schools and universities across the world - and every day, we hear from scores of institutions who are interested in the MediaCore platform. We&rsquo;re recruiting for a Sales Support Coordinator, who will be the first point of contact for these institutions. You&rsquo;ll be working closely with our Education Team to ensure every customer has an elegant sales experience - and contributing to MediaCore&rsquo;s success by ensuring that every opportunity is acted on.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Being the first port of call for incoming sales inquiries</li>
<li>
Qualifying, triaging, and responding to incoming leads as appropriate</li>
<li>
Working with the Education Team to ensure that larger opportunities are successfully passed off and followed up by the most appropriate team member(s)</li>
<li>
Working with our CRM (Salesforce) to ensure that incoming inquiries are properly logged, tracked and documented.</li>
<li>
Handling individual school sales</li>
<li>
Guiding schools through the sales process, from initial inquiry to a successful sale.</li>
<li>
Overseeing free teacher account signups</li>
<li>
Personally reaching out to teachers who have signed up</li>
<li>
Handing off support and training issues to the Support Team</li>
<li>
Identifying opportunities within the free teacher account portfolio, and escalating these to the Education Team</li>
<li>
Tastefully promoting the benefits of whole-school MediaCore deployments to teachers who have engaged with the free platform</li>
<li>
Overseeing targeted email campaigns</li>
<li>
Working with the Director of Marketing and Education Team to identify and execute targeted email campaigns that drive the sales pipeline</li>
<li>
Qualifying,triaging and responding to all campaign responses as appropriate</li>
<li>
Tracking the effectiveness of campaigns</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Attributes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Some inside sales experience</li>
<li>
Knowledge of the education space</li>
<li>
Exemplary written skills</li>
<li>
Confident, approachable communicator via all channels</li>
<li>
Technically minded, able to explain concepts in a simple, approachable way</li>
<li>
